quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  41,30,"Surely, those who say: “Our Lord is God,” and then go straight, the angels will descend upon them: “Do not fear, and do not grieve, but rejoice in the news of the Garden which you were promised"
  41,31,"We are your allies in this life and in the Hereafter, wherein you will have whatever your souls desire, and you will have therein whatever you call for"
  41,32,"As Hospitality from an All-Forgiving, Merciful One.”"
  41,33,"And who is better in speech than someone who calls to God, and acts with integrity, and says, “I am of those who submit”"
  41,34,"Good and evil are not equal. Repel evil with good, and the person who was your enemy becomes like an intimate friend"
  41,35,"But none will attain it except those who persevere, and none will attain it except the very fortunate"
  41,36,"When a temptation from the Devil provokes you, seek refuge in God; He is the Hearer, the Knower"
  41,37,"And of His signs are the night and the day, and the sun and the moon. Do not bow down to the sun, nor to the moon, but bow down to God, Who created them both, if it is Him that you serve"
  41,38,"But if they are too proud—those in the presence of your Lord praise Him night and day, and without ever tiring"